    "problemStatement": "Chef had NNN rupees with him.\n\nHe decided to buy AAA ice creams for his friends, each at a cost of BBB rupees. He was able to pay the entire amount.\n\nFind how many rupees Chef still has left with him at the end?\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first and only line of input contains 333 integers - N,AN, AN,A and BBB.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line the amount of rupees Chef has left.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264N\u226410001 \\le N \\le 10001\u2264N\u22641000",
      "1\u2264A,B\u22641001 \\le A, B \\le 1001\u2264A,B\u2264100",
      "A\u22c5B\u2264NA \\cdot B \\le NA\u22c5B\u2264N"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
